    {
      "type": "text",
      "version": 2,
      "id": "your_approach_body",
      "x": 80,
      "y": 475,
      "width": 270,
      "height": 120,
      "text": "1. Data is STRUCTURED (rows/cols)\n   → SQL is perfect for this\n\n2. Schema fits in LLM context\n   → No need to \"retrieve\" it\n\n3. SQL gives EXACT answers\n   → Vector search gives fuzzy ones\n\n4. No embeddings overhead needed",
      "fontSize": 11,
      "fontFamily": 1,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "strokeColor": "#2f9e44",
